132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 707
H.P. 446 House of Representatives, February 25, 2025
An Act to Amend the Membership of the State Employee Health
Commission and Make Referential Changes to the Office of
Employee Health, Wellness and Workers' Compensation
Submitted by the Department of Administrative and Financial Services pursuant to Joint
Rule 204.
Received by the Clerk of the House on February 20, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Health Coverage, Insurance and Financial Services pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered
printed pursuant to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative MATHIESON of Kittery.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 PART A
3 Sec. A-1. 5 MRSA §285-A, sub-§2, as amended by PL 2021, c. 312, §3 and c. 548,
4 §45, is further amended to read:
5 2. Membership. The State Employee Health Commission consists of 24 labor and
6 management members as follows:
7 A. One labor member from each bargaining unit recognized under Title 26, chapter
8 9‑B, appointed by the employee organization certified to represent the unit;
9 B. One labor member from the largest bargaining unit recognized under Title 26,
10 chapter 14, appointed by the employee organization authorized to represent the unit;
11 C. One labor member appointed by the retiree chapters of the Maine State Employees
12 Association;
13 C-1. One labor member from Maine Turnpike Authority employees appointed by the
14 employee organization authorized to represent the employees;
15 C-2. One labor member from Maine Public Employees Retirement System employees,
16 appointed by the employee organization authorized to represent the employees;
17 C-3. One labor member from Maine Maritime Academy employees, appointed by the
18 employee organization authorized to represent the employees;
19 D. Four management members appointed by the Commissioner of Administrative and
20 Financial Services;
21 E. One management member appointed by the Court Administrators;
22 F. The Executive Director of Employee Health and, Wellness and Workers'
23 Compensation, ex officio;
24 F-1. The State Human Resources Officer, ex officio;
25 G. One member representing retirees appointed by the Maine Association of Retirees;
26 H. One labor member from the Maine Community College System faculty or
27 administrative unit, appointed by the employee organization authorized to represent
28 the units;
29 I. One management member from the Maine Community College System appointed
30 by the President of the Maine Community College System;
31 J. One management member appointed by the Executive Director of the Maine
32 Turnpike Authority;
33 K. One management member appointed by the Chief Executive Officer of the Maine
34 Public Employees Retirement System; and
35 L. One management member appointed by the President of the Maine Maritime
36 Academy.
37 All appointed or elected members serve at the pleasure of their appointing or electing
38 authorities.
