4 Sec. B-6. 5 MRSA §286-N, sub-§3, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 446, §5, is amended
5 to read:
6 3. Chair. The executive director of the office of employee health and benefits
7 Executive Director of Employee Health, Wellness and Workers' Compensation within the
8 Department of Administrative and Financial Services, Bureau of Human Resources, or the
9 executive director's designee, shall serve as chair.
10 Sec. B-7. 20-A MRSA §13451, sub-§3, as amended by PL 2023, c. 412, Pt.
11 OOOOO, §§1 to 3, is further amended by amending the 2nd blocked paragraph to read:
12 A provider of a health insurance benefit plan for retired teachers must make available data
13 related to the provider's premium costs and any related data as requested by the Executive
14 Director of Employee Health and, Wellness and Workers' Compensation within the
15 Department of Administrative and Financial Services.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This bill adds a member to the State Employee Health Commission and changes the
1188 name of the Office of Employee Health and Wellness within the Department of
1199 Administrative and Financial Services to the Office of Employee Health, Wellness and
2200 Workers' Compensation.
21 Part A of the bill adds the State Human Resources Officer as an ex officio member of
22 the State Employee Health Commission. It also provides that the management cochair of
23 the commission is designated by the Commissioner of Administrative and Financial
24 Services from among the management members appointed by the Commissioner of
25 Administrative and Financial Services.
26 Part B of the bill replaces statutory references to the Office of Employee Health and
27 Wellness and its executive director with the office's new title.
